libquo
------------------------------------------
QUO (as in 'status quo') is a runtime library that aids in accommodating
thread-level heterogeneity in dynamic, phased MPI+X applications comprising
single- and multi-threaded libraries.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.2-1
  libgcc1-7.4.0-1
  libgfortran4-7.4.0-1
  libopenmpi40-3.1.5-1
  libquo-devel-1.3.1-1bl1
  libquo7-1.3.1-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-fortran-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-7
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/lanl/libquo

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/lanl/libquo/archive/v1.3.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libquo-1.3.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libquo-1.3.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libquo-1.3.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libquo-1.3.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libquo7-1.3.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libquo-devel-1.3.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libquo)
  /usr/bin/quo-info.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libquo.README
  /usr/share/doc/libquo/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libquo/COPYRIGHT
  /usr/share/doc/libquo/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/libquo/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/libquo/THANKS
  /usr/share/doc/libquo/TODO

(libquo7)
  /usr/bin/cygquo-7.dll
  /usr/bin/cygquo-usequo-7.dll

(libquo-devel)
  /usr/include/quo.h
  /usr/include/quo.mod
  /usr/lib/libquo-usequo.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libquo.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libquo.pc

